<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="enveloped_virus">Enveloped Virus</a> - A <a href="#virus">virus</a> that has an outer wrapping known as an envelope. These <a href="#virus">viruses</a> are wrapped in what was before the <a href="#host">host</a>'s <a href="#lipidBilayer">plasma membrane</a> which is obtained in a process known as budding-off. Typically enveloped viruses are much weaker when exposed to the environment and need a host to survive. They do not survive on sterile surfaces.